Gun sales are booming nationwide ‰ÛÓ and in Erie County, applications for pistol permits are rolling in at nearly three times last year's rate, the county clerk's office reports. Meanwhile, in the nation's capital, gun control has become, in essence, dead on arrival. Chalk it all up to the election of a Democratic president with a long record of supporting gun restrictions and a Congress that includes a surprising number of pro-gun Democrats from rural areas. The election of Barack Obama as president is sparking a run on firearms and ammunition in both Buffalo and nationwide, according to gun dealers and experts on the issue.